text: Zoya Ananchenko (born September 5, 1996) is a Kazakhstani sprint canoeist. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's K-1 500 metres race, in which she reached the semifinals, and as part of the tenth-place Kazakhstan team in the women's K-4 500 metres race. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Kazakhstani female canoeists Category:Olympic canoeists of Kazakhstan Category:Canoeists at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Asian Games medalists in canoeing Category:Canoeists at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Canoeists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games
